  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "8",
      "note": "For my rendering of thumma at the beginning of this verse as \"And once again\", see surah 6, note 31. The repetition of this rhetorical question is meant to indicate that man's intellect and imagination cannot possibly answer it, since what is described as the Day of Judgment will usher in a reality which as yet is wholly outside our human experience and, therefore, cannot be grasped conceptually: hence, only allegory - and our own emotional response to it - can give us an inkling of what that reality might be."
